Sometimes  my dad is too harsh.

Like Today, Dad picked me up from the band hall, as we were walking to the car, Dad's like "So how'd u do?" 
I say, " I got one away from Zone Band."
"Zone Band"
So I explained to him what that means.
"Why'd you get that score?"
"Nervousness"
And here's the harsh part: "Taylor! You gotta quit with this Nervousness crap!" (mean, huh?!")
So... I walk to the car without an expression on my face.
"Taylor, don't look @ me like that."
"Dad, I didn't do anything!!!!"
He looks at me, and gets in the drivers seat.
He tells me something, but I wasn't paying attention... something to do with being happy with my score...
"Dad, I'm fine with my score..."

eghhh... Fathers can be rough around the edges.......
